Staff needs to be properly informed on how to serve up their nitro cold brew. I get it, it's their first day of having the nitro cold brew available at this location and the gentleman (Nevin or Kevin?) who took my order told me I can't get a Venti size when I inquired (I know this and am aware of this fact at all Starbucks locations for the nitro but wanted to test his knowledge). Of course I acted like it was my first time ordering the nitro brew and proceeded to get the one with cascara foam. I watched the other gentleman pour nitro up to the top 3rd black line, which is 8 oz out of the 16 oz grande sized cup. That's half cold brew and half freaking sweet foam. You gotta be kidding me, I requested less foam and he tells me that it was up to the third line and he already made it - yes I know, I saw you pour it. He dumps out the cup and pours another, this time a little over the top line and unwillingly serves it like 90% fullish. I'm not paying close to 6 bucks for half a cup of cascara foam. On my way out, the first gentleman calls me out (with customers in line!) and tells me "it's for health reasons due to caffeine by the way," I responded that it's supposed to be full if I ordered without the foam right and he says 'nah nah' - total BS, the drink doesn't even contain more than 250 mg of caffeine esp with 1/3rd foam in it. The real reason is volume and how many sales out of a certain keg. The staff needs to know this along with how to serve portions properly and quit playing dumb with the customers. Foam should be one inch below the rim, if that and no more, that's what those ridged lines are for on the cups.

By that time I couldn’t believe their attitude so I asked again in a loud voice, only to be ignored again. One girl came from the back and asked me what i needed and gave me ice right away with a nice smile. How these other lazy and incompetent people work there is beyond me ! I would have asked for a manager but I did not want to embarrass my guests any further. What a shameful staff you have in that Starbucks ! I guess I need to rethink all the money I spend in that chain.

I'm staying in the Marriott Renaissance hotel where the Starbucks is located. For the past few days, I have been getting my coffee from the Starbucks located 1.5 blocks away in the Marriott Marquis where the conference is being held. I have been paying $6 for a coffee and bagel and even though it is always very busy, customer service has been pleasant. Today, I decided to just order at this Starbucks since there wasn't a long line. William took my order. Although he wasn't rude, he certainly was not friendly or welcoming. He should have a role that would require less customer interaction. His two colleagues who were making the orders seemed to have better customer service skills based on my short interaction with them.  When he charged me for my order, I realized it was close to $9 for the same exact meal I have been ordering the last few days. I asked are the prices higher here to which he responded "I don't know how much other Starbucks charge, but yes the prices are generally higher here." The coffee and bagel were normal Starbucks quality but not worth the extra cost especially with so many Starbucks locations in the area. I can understand price differences from city to city but not a $3 difference within a 1.5 block radius. Do yourself a favor, choose another location.

About 2 weeks ago I saw a worker cleaning a umbrella and he was talking to that guy that always sits on the bench and I happened to stop and listen and they seemed like they were having fun talking. I could not understand what he was saying sometimes but he mad my day. I used to work for Starbucks back in the 90s and he reminded me of myself working had knowing he had that things has to get done. It was like 50 degrees outside and he was smiling and making the best out of his day. I felt bad for that man on the bench and brought him a coffee and sandwich. Kudos to the staff for the effort you put in for people like me just to get thru the day.
